        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Define the DocumentContent data structure — the primary container for a document&apos;s parsed text (as a tree) and tables. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Structured document content: text tree, tables, warnings. \par \b Input\/ \:  Tables list, TreeNode root, optional warnings. \par \b Output\/ \:  DocumentContent instance convertible to API schema. \par \b Links\/ \:  [INHERITS(5): Serializable, USES_API(8): ApiDocumentContent, READS_DATA_FROM(9): Table, TreeNode] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>warnings is never None (defaults to empty list) \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why separate tables from the text tree structure? A: Tables have a fundamentally different data model (grid vs tree), and keeping them separate simplifies both storage and API representation. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
